FBIS4-23907 "drafr118_c_94012" FBIS-AFR-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA MK Integration To Cost 132 Million Rands MK Integration To Cost 132 Million Rands MB1706164394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 17 Jun 94 MB1706164394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The integration of Umkhonto we Sizwe [Spear of the Nation; MK -- ANC armed wing] into the National Defense Force is reported to be going smoothly now, and more than 3,000 members of the former armed wing of the ANC will begin their training at Wallmansthall near Pretoria on Monday. The integration of MK into the defense force will cost an estimated 132 million rands. Negotiations on the integration of APLA [Azanian People's Liberation Army] are under way at the moment.
